casebody.data:
Carl E. GABRIEL
v.
DELTA AIRLINES, INC. and ACE American Insurance Company No. 2017-C-1990 Supreme Court of Louisiana. January 29, 2018 ON WRIT OF CERTIORARI TO THE COURT OF APPEAL, FIFTH CIRCUIT, OFFICE OF WORKERS' COMPENSATION, DISTRICT 7 Writ denied. HUGHES, J., concurs with reasons. Hughes, J. concurring.

Respondent in its opposition represents that the radiofrequency nerve ablation sought by applicant "has been authorized and paid for by Defendant/Appellee", essentially rendering this matter moot.
